description:
Hi,
I think I found a bug with the SPARQL 1.1 Update implementation in VOS 7.1.
The problem appears to be that if an object has a datatype xsd:int then it doesn't get deleted by a WITH... DELETE query.
Here are the sparql queries you can use in iSQL that will replicate the issue:
sparql clear graph <http://test.com/tests/>;

sparql
insert data
{
  graph <http://test.com/tests/> {
    <http://foo.com/datasets/tests/foo> <http://purl.org/ontology/wsf#product_in_inventory> "9"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#int> .
  }
};

sparql
select *
from <http://test.com/tests/>
where
{
  ?s ?p ?o .
};

sparql
with <http://test.com/tests/>
delete
{
  <http://foo.com/datasets/tests/foo> <http://purl.org/ontology/wsf#product_in_inventory> ?o .
}
where
{
  <http://foo.com/datasets/tests/foo> <http://purl.org/ontology/wsf#product_in_inventory> ?o .
};

sparql
select *
from <http://test.com/tests/>
where
{
  ?s ?p ?o .
};

As you can see, the triple is still there when we run the last SPARQL query. If we don't mention any datatype (or if you mention xsd:string, or xsd:dateTime, or whatever) it gets deleted:
sparql clear graph <http://test.com/tests/>;

sparql
insert data
{
  graph <http://test.com/tests/> {
    <http://foo.com/datasets/tests/foo> <http://purl.org/ontology/wsf#product_in_inventory> "9" .
  }
};

sparql
select *
from <http://test.com/tests/>
where
{
  ?s ?p ?o .
};

sparql
with <http://test.com/tests/>
delete
{
  <http://foo.com/datasets/tests/foo> <http://purl.org/ontology/wsf#product_in_inventory> ?o .
}
where
{
  <http://foo.com/datasets/tests/foo> <http://purl.org/ontology/wsf#product_in_inventory> ?o .
};

sparql
select *
from <http://test.com/tests/>
where
{
  ?s ?p ?o .
};

Question one: if there a work around that would work the same way but with another syntax that doesn't trigger the bug?
Also note that the same query (but using delete from) SPARQL query was working as expected with VOS 6.x.
Thanks
Fred
